WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.120 --> 00:00:02.690
Congratulations on what
a final game that was.

00:00:02.690 --> 00:00:06.450
&gt;&gt; Thank you.
&gt;&gt; You could not have dreamed of anything

00:00:06.450 --> 00:00:07.490
like that right?

00:00:07.490 --> 00:00:08.330
&gt;&gt; Not for sure.

00:00:08.330 --> 00:00:12.365
I mean it was I couldn't believe
that it actually happened.

00:00:12.365 --> 00:00:16.070
At this moment was actually here and
this is the game.

00:00:16.070 --> 00:00:16.670
&gt;&gt; Yeah.

00:00:16.670 --> 00:00:18.970
&gt;&gt; It was really it's kind
of a strange feeling.

00:00:18.970 --> 00:00:21.110
&gt;&gt; I know when you were walking out,

00:00:21.110 --> 00:00:24.385
I mean you must have been emotional
when you woke up that day right?

00:00:24.385 --> 00:00:25.745
&gt;&gt; No, I was pretty calm.

00:00:25.745 --> 00:00:26.790
Because it doesn't really dawn on you.

00:00:26.790 --> 00:00:29.160
Then, when I walked in the arena, and
you kind of feel the electricity?

00:00:29.160 --> 00:00:30.860
&gt;&gt; Yeah.
&gt;&gt; And you just kind of

00:00:30.860 --> 00:00:32.250
start getting a little nostalgic.

00:00:32.250 --> 00:00:33.400
&gt;&gt; Yeah.
&gt;&gt; Then you realize,

00:00:33.400 --> 00:00:35.510
everybody's here to watch this final game.

00:00:35.510 --> 00:00:36.250
Don't suck.

00:00:36.250 --> 00:00:37.240
&gt;&gt; Yeah.

00:00:37.240 --> 00:00:37.765
Yeah.
&gt;&gt; [LAUGH]

00:00:37.765 --> 00:00:39.155
&gt;&gt; It's like you gotta make sure you,

00:00:39.155 --> 00:00:41.655
and then I come out and
I miss my first five shots.

00:00:41.655 --> 00:00:42.550
I was like uh-oh.

00:00:42.550 --> 00:00:44.055
&gt;&gt; Yeah well that's the thing

00:00:44.055 --> 00:00:46.560
then it could really screw
with you because if you're not

00:00:46.560 --> 00:00:49.362
hitting it right away then you're like,
you'd unravel.

00:00:49.362 --> 00:00:51.590
&gt;&gt; Yeah, but the last game,
you just say you know what?

00:00:51.590 --> 00:00:54.210
I'm just gonna go out there and
let it all hang loose.

00:00:54.210 --> 00:00:57.190
&gt;&gt; And when you see all those celebrities,
I mean they're there a lot anyway,

00:00:57.190 --> 00:01:01.200
but does that distract you at all when
you look over and you see somebody?

00:01:01.200 --> 00:01:05.050
&gt;&gt; No, it's fun it's just adds to
the excitement and adds to the focus.

00:01:05.050 --> 00:01:08.805
And I was on the bench I heard your
voice come up on a jumbotron.

00:01:08.805 --> 00:01:12.020
&gt;&gt; [LAUGH]
&gt;&gt; Hey, they got Ellen up there too.

00:01:12.020 --> 00:01:13.330
&gt;&gt; When I was saying goodbye to you.

00:01:13.330 --> 00:01:14.270
&gt;&gt; Yeah.
&gt;&gt; Yeah, that was funny.

00:01:14.270 --> 00:01:15.620
&gt;&gt; That was pretty that was funny.

00:01:15.620 --> 00:01:18.490
&gt;&gt; I don't think you might would even hear
it coz, it's gonna be so noisy on there.

00:01:18.490 --> 00:01:20.800
&gt;&gt; No, I mean the fresh prince is such a catchy,

00:01:20.800 --> 00:01:21.740
&gt;&gt; Yeah.
&gt;&gt; Catchy tune.

00:01:21.740 --> 00:01:24.070
&gt;&gt; Thank you Thank you very much.

00:01:24.070 --> 00:01:25.630
Anyway.
&gt;&gt; [LAUGH]

00:01:25.630 --> 00:01:27.130
&gt;&gt; So your daughters were there and

00:01:27.130 --> 00:01:28.590
that must have been really cool.

00:01:28.590 --> 00:01:31.510
I mean, had they seen you play like that?

00:01:31.510 --> 00:01:34.900
&gt;&gt; No, they haven't and they was like,
dad where did that come from?

00:01:34.900 --> 00:01:37.970
And I was like, well honey I
used to be pretty good back in

00:01:37.970 --> 00:01:38.785
the day when you're like.

00:01:38.785 --> 00:01:42.360
&gt;&gt; [LAUGH]
&gt;&gt; They thought it was pretty awesome.

00:01:42.360 --> 00:01:45.940
I think the coolest thing for
them is me walking out just now and

00:01:45.940 --> 00:01:48.290
not embarrassing them completely.

00:01:48.290 --> 00:01:50.035
By not dancing pathetically.

00:01:50.035 --> 00:01:52.590
&gt;&gt; [LAUGH]
&gt;&gt; Do you really never dance?

00:01:52.590 --> 00:01:53.250
&gt;&gt; Or maybe I did.

00:01:53.250 --> 00:01:54.530
&gt;&gt; No, you didn't.
It was a swag.

00:01:54.530 --> 00:01:55.850
It was a little bit of a.

00:01:55.850 --> 00:01:57.800
You can't go wrong if you just pose and
do that.

00:01:57.800 --> 00:01:58.770
&gt;&gt; Right.
That's what I figured.

00:01:58.770 --> 00:02:00.630
I kinda just stick to my one-two,
you know what I mean?

00:02:00.630 --> 00:02:02.810
Make sure I don't completely
embarrass my children.

00:02:02.810 --> 00:02:03.440
&gt;&gt; Do you ever dance?

00:02:03.440 --> 00:02:04.310
&gt;&gt; Yes.

00:02:04.310 --> 00:02:04.990
Of course.

00:02:04.990 --> 00:02:06.695
&gt;&gt; You do.
&gt;&gt; Yeah, but I'm a better sit down dancer.

00:02:06.695 --> 00:02:08.020
&gt;&gt; [LAUGHING]
&gt;&gt; Everybody is.

00:02:08.020 --> 00:02:09.020
&gt;&gt; Know what I'm saying?

00:02:09.020 --> 00:02:10.990
Like, from here on down,
this does not work.

00:02:10.990 --> 00:02:13.600
But like, up here,
I could sit here and dance all day.

00:02:13.600 --> 00:02:14.428
You think thing like.

00:02:14.428 --> 00:02:16.190
&gt;&gt; [LAUGH]
&gt;&gt; Like me and Twitch like you feel like I

00:02:16.190 --> 00:02:17.610
could battle Twitch and like
&gt;&gt; Yeah.

00:02:17.610 --> 00:02:18.261
&gt;&gt; Maybe win or something.

00:02:18.261 --> 00:02:20.590
&gt;&gt; [LAUGH]
&gt;&gt; But once I stand up it doesn't connect.

00:02:20.590 --> 00:02:22.850
&gt;&gt; Wow when you sit down
you do that with your hand?

00:02:22.850 --> 00:02:24.230
&gt;&gt; Yeah I can like do that and

00:02:24.230 --> 00:02:26.400
it's like he looks like he knows
what he's doing but no I don't.

00:02:26.400 --> 00:02:27.800
&gt;&gt; You do know what you're doing.

00:02:27.800 --> 00:02:29.880
&gt;&gt; You got.
&gt;&gt; Nobody sit dances doing that.

00:02:29.880 --> 00:02:32.111
We all just kind of bob our
heads that's all we do.

00:02:32.111 --> 00:02:33.134
&gt;&gt; [LAUGH]
&gt;&gt; Yeah listen.

00:02:33.134 --> 00:02:35.994
Hey if you wanna ever have a sit
down dance battle I'm all for it.

00:02:35.994 --> 00:02:37.390
&gt;&gt; I'm down.
&gt;&gt; [LAUGH]

00:02:37.390 --> 00:02:37.910
&gt;&gt; I'm down.

00:02:37.910 --> 00:02:40.085
&gt;&gt; I think we'd all like to see that.

00:02:40.085 --> 00:02:46.290
&gt;&gt; [APPLAUSE]
&gt;&gt; No, I'm kidding, I'm kidding.

00:02:46.290 --> 00:02:49.350
&gt;&gt; So Shaq was here the other
day on your final day.

00:02:49.350 --> 00:02:53.870
And he said basically
y'all were not battling,

00:02:53.870 --> 00:02:57.900
that you just inspired each other and
pushed each other to work harder.

00:02:57.900 --> 00:02:58.410
&gt;&gt; Yeah.

00:02:58.410 --> 00:02:59.590
&gt;&gt; Is that what happened?

00:02:59.590 --> 00:03:03.830
&gt;&gt; No, I didn't really like him too much.

00:03:03.830 --> 00:03:05.000
[LAUGH]
&gt;&gt; You didn't like him?

00:03:05.000 --> 00:03:06.230
&gt;&gt; No, I'm kidding.

00:03:06.230 --> 00:03:07.720
He's-
&gt;&gt; Are you?

00:03:07.720 --> 00:03:08.847
&gt;&gt; No I am.
&gt;&gt; [LAUGH]

00:03:08.847 --> 00:03:10.475
&gt;&gt; But we challenge each other a lot.

00:03:10.475 --> 00:03:10.980
&gt;&gt; Mm-hm.
&gt;&gt; And

00:03:11.520 --> 00:03:14.420
I think in any environment you wanna have,

00:03:14.420 --> 00:03:16.660
people around you that are not gonna
just tell you which you want to hear.

00:03:16.660 --> 00:03:17.690
&gt;&gt; Mm-hm.
&gt;&gt; I mean they're going to be

00:03:17.690 --> 00:03:18.610
honest with you.

00:03:18.610 --> 00:03:21.830
&gt;&gt; Yep.
&gt;&gt; We certainly were that with each other.

00:03:21.830 --> 00:03:23.310
&gt;&gt; Yeah and now you're friends?

00:03:23.310 --> 00:03:24.560
&gt;&gt; Yeah we get along just fine.

00:03:24.560 --> 00:03:25.590
&gt;&gt; Yeah.

00:03:25.590 --> 00:03:28.307
&gt;&gt; Yeah, we don't share the same
work environment either.

00:03:28.307 --> 00:03:28.980
Yeah, that's always good.

00:03:28.980 --> 00:03:35.010
&gt;&gt; Yeah well you're amazing and thank you
for being here for the first interview.

00:03:35.010 --> 00:03:37.028
We're gonna take a break and
more with Kobe and

00:03:37.028 --> 00:03:39.791
a surprise a little later that will
be fun for all of us to watch.

00:03:39.791 --> 00:03:49.791
&gt;&gt; [MUSIC]

00:03:56.224 --> 00:04:01.430
&gt;&gt; [APPLAUSE]
&gt;&gt; How many times have you watched that?

00:04:01.430 --> 00:04:02.450
Did you go home and watch it?

00:04:02.450 --> 00:04:03.000
&gt;&gt; A few times, yeah.

00:04:03.000 --> 00:04:03.690
&gt;&gt; Yeah.

00:04:03.690 --> 00:04:05.050
&gt;&gt; But I'm such a basketball nerd.

00:04:05.050 --> 00:04:07.480
Like I went back and watched it and
I'm like picking it apart.

00:04:07.480 --> 00:04:09.070
My footwork was wrong there.

00:04:09.070 --> 00:04:10.240
Or I should have did that.

00:04:10.240 --> 00:04:11.210
Well, there's no backsies now.

00:04:11.210 --> 00:04:11.980
&gt;&gt; Yeah.
&gt;&gt; So it really doesn't

00:04:11.980 --> 00:04:12.610
matter at this point.

00:04:12.610 --> 00:04:13.260
&gt;&gt; No.

00:04:13.260 --> 00:04:14.370
&gt;&gt; But I think everybody does that.

00:04:14.370 --> 00:04:16.830
We all watch ourselves, and
see things that nobody else sees.

00:04:16.830 --> 00:04:17.910
&gt;&gt; Yeah.
&gt;&gt; But that was amazing, and

00:04:17.910 --> 00:04:22.711
that must be so much fun to do, and then
to look back at it, but then no regrets.

00:04:22.711 --> 00:04:24.430
Right?
You think this is the right time?

00:04:24.430 --> 00:04:26.810
&gt;&gt; Yeah, it feels right to me.

00:04:26.810 --> 00:04:28.880
I'm very blessed to be able to say that.

00:04:28.880 --> 00:04:30.670
I just don't wanna play anymore.

00:04:30.670 --> 00:04:32.200
It's not like my body forced me out.

00:04:32.200 --> 00:04:33.130
I don't wanna do it anymore.

00:04:33.130 --> 00:04:34.860
I'm ready to move on.

00:04:34.860 --> 00:04:37.390
&gt;&gt; And will you still play recreationally?

00:04:37.390 --> 00:04:38.450
Right.
&gt;&gt; Yeah, probably.

00:04:38.450 --> 00:04:40.300
&gt;&gt; Yeah, you have a court at your house,
I assume?

00:04:40.300 --> 00:04:42.930
&gt;&gt; I do.
&gt;&gt; So, do you just go out and shoot hoops.

00:04:42.930 --> 00:04:45.390
&gt;&gt; Yeah, yeah me, my wife, and
our kids, we'll go out and shoot.

00:04:45.390 --> 00:04:47.210
And a-
&gt;&gt; Is she good, your wife?

00:04:47.210 --> 00:04:48.290
&gt;&gt; Yeah, she can shoot, actually.

00:04:48.290 --> 00:04:48.990
&gt;&gt; Really.
&gt;&gt; She can shoot,

00:04:48.990 --> 00:04:50.710
my kids can shoot too, so.

00:04:50.710 --> 00:04:51.290
&gt;&gt; Really.
&gt;&gt; Yeah.

00:04:51.290 --> 00:04:54.800
&gt;&gt; Would you want your kids
to go into this profession.

00:04:54.800 --> 00:04:56.690
&gt;&gt; Man, if they wanted to,
if they wanted to.

00:04:56.690 --> 00:04:57.190
&gt;&gt; Do they?

00:04:58.250 --> 00:05:01.270
&gt;&gt; Well the little one's really,
really competitive.

00:05:02.580 --> 00:05:05.413
And she likes playing sports,
and so we'll see,

00:05:05.413 --> 00:05:08.596
oldest one she loves playing volleyball so
we'll see.

